-- South African Bus Accident Kills 16, Injures 31, SAPA Reports
-- B y   M i k e   C o h e n
-- 2012-07-21T09:29:26Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-21/south-african-bus-accident-kills-16-injures-31-sapa-reports.html
A collision between two buses
traveling on a road between the towns of Cradock and Graaf-
Reinet in southeastern  South Africa  claimed the lives of 16
people, the South Africa Press Association reported, citing
Tshepo Machaea, a spokesman for the road safety campaign, Arrive
Alive.  Four people were badly hurt in the crash, while 27
sustained minor injuries, Machaea said, according to the
Johannesburg-based news agency.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Mike Cohen in Cape Town at 
